Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_stress_rule(25.10)                            create_stress_rule(25.10)

Name
       create_stress_rule - Defines a spacing table for spacing rules

Syntax
       create_stress_rule

       [-help]

       { {-layer <layerName> -spacing_table <spacing_table> [-chip_name <chip-
       Name>]} | [-reset ] }

       Defines  a  spacing  table  for  spacing  rules. Since the spacing rule
       varies with the location of the keep out zone in the chip, user can de-
       fine different spacing tables for different spacing rule. These spacing
       tables are used by the tool to identify different scenarios and  select
       the correct spacing constraint for a scenario.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the create_stress_rule command us-
              age.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man create_stress_rule

       -chip_name chipName
              Specifies  the  name  of the chip for which the spacing table is
              used for checking violation. If this option  is  not  specified,
              the  tool  applies the spacing rule for all the chips above, be-
              low, and current based on the masterslice  layer  definition  in
              the LEF file

       -layer <layerName>
              Specifies the name of the stress layer for which the spacing ta-
              ble is used for checking violation.

       -reset Resets all stress rules.

       -spacing_table <spacing_table>
              Specifies the spacing table definition, {x1 y1} {x2 y2}.

